{
  "video_id": "R84vqXjXWJc",
  "title": "Black life at the intersection of birth and death | Mwende \"FreeQuency\" Katwiwa",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12560.0,
      "end_time": 14719.0,
      "text": "My name is Mwende Katwiwa"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15680.0,
      "end_time": 17136.0,
      "text": "and I am a poet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17160.0,
      "end_time": 18576.0,
      "text": "a Pan-Africanist"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 18600.0,
      "end_time": 20800.0,
      "text": "and a freedom fighter."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 21000.0,
      "end_time": 22376.0,
      "text": "I was 23 years old"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 22400.0,
      "end_time": 24680.0,
      "text": "when I first heard about Reproductive Justice."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 25440.0,
      "end_time": 27576.0,
      "text": "I was working at Women with a Vision,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 27600.0,
      "end_time": 31656.0,
      "text": "where I learned that Reproductive Justice was defined by Sister Song as:"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 31680.0,
      "end_time": 36960.0,
      "text": "One: A woman&#39;s right to decide if and when she will have a baby"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 36120.0,
      "end_time": 38736.0,
      "text": "and the conditions under which she will give birth."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 38760.0,
      "end_time": 42336.0,
      "text": "Two: A woman&#39;s right to decide if she will not have a baby"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 42360.0,
      "end_time": 45456.0,
      "text": "and her options for preventing or ending a pregnancy."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 45480.0,
      "end_time": 49616.0,
      "text": "And three: A woman&#39;s right to parent the children she already has"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 49640.0,
      "end_time": 51416.0,
      "text": "in safe and healthy environments"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 51440.0,
      "end_time": 53135.0,
      "text": "without fear of violence"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 53160.0,
      "end_time": 55239.0,
      "text": "from individuals or the government."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56320.0,
      "end_time": 58000.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve always wanted to be a mother."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 59440.0,
      "end_time": 62896.0,
      "text": "Growing up, I heard all about the joys of motherhood."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 62920.0,
      "end_time": 66320.0,
      "text": "I used to dream of watching my womb weave wonder into this world."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 67400.0,
      "end_time": 68736.0,
      "text": "See, I knew I was young."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 68760.0,
      "end_time": 69976.0,
      "text": "But I figured,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 70000.0,
      "end_time": 73520.0,
      "text": "it couldn&#39;t hurt to start planning for something so big, so early."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 75200.0,
      "end_time": 76400.0,
      "text": "But now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 77319.0,
      "end_time": 78760.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m 26 years old."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 79400.0,
      "end_time": 83160.0,
      "text": "And I don&#39;t know if I have what it takes to stomach motherhood in this country."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 83760.0,
      "end_time": 86736.0,
      "text": "See, over the years, America has taught me more about parenting"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 86760.0,
      "end_time": 88536.0,
      "text": "than any book on the subject."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 88560.0,
      "end_time": 91160.0,
      "text": "It has taught me how some women give birth to babies"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 91400.0,
      "end_time": 92936.0,
      "text": "and others to suspects."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 92960.0,
      "end_time": 95535.0,
      "text": "It has taught me that this body will birth kin"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 95560.0,
      "end_time": 98136.0,
      "text": "who are more likely to be held in prison cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 98160.0,
      "end_time": 100160.0,
      "text": "than to hold college degrees."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 100720.0,
      "end_time": 104456.0,
      "text": "There is something about being Black in America"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 104480.0,
      "end_time": 105880.0,
      "text": "that has made motherhood seem"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 107160.0,
      "end_time": 108360.0,
      "text": "complicated."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 109480.0,
      "end_time": 110696.0,
      "text": "Seem like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 110720.0,
      "end_time": 112896.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know what to do to raise my kids right"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 112920.0,
      "end_time": 114256.0,
      "text": "and keep them alive."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 114280.0,
      "end_time": 116816.0,
      "text": "Do I tell my son not to steal because it is wrong,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 116840.0,
      "end_time": 119160.0,
      "text": "or because they will use it to justify his death?"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 119800.0,
      "end_time": 121150.0,
      "text": "Do I tell him"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 121400.0,
      "end_time": 123616.0,
      "text": "that even if he pays for his Skittles and sweet tea"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 123640.0,
      "end_time": 125736.0,
      "text": "there will still be those who will watch him"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 125760.0,
      "end_time": 128256.0,
      "text": "and see a criminal before child;"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 128280.0,
      "end_time": 131216.0,
      "text": "who will call the police and not wait for them to come."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 131240.0,
      "end_time": 133456.0,
      "text": "Do I even want the police to come?"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 133480.0,
      "end_time": 137495.0,
      "text": "Too many Sean Bells go off in my head when I consider calling 911."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 137520.0,
      "end_time": 141400.0,
      "text": "I will not take it for Oscar Grant-ed that they will not come and kill my son."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 141919.0,
      "end_time": 144960.0,
      "text": "So, we may have gotten rid of the nooses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 144120.0,
      "end_time": 146976.0,
      "text": "but I still consider it lynching when they murder Black boys"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 147000.0,
      "end_time": 149320.0,
      "text": "and leave their bodies for four hours in the sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 150400.0,
      "end_time": 152215.0,
      "text": "As a historical reminder"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 152240.0,
      "end_time": 155856.0,
      "text": "that there is something about being Black in America"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 155880.0,
      "end_time": 157775.0,
      "text": "that has made motherhood sound"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 157800.0,
      "end_time": 159160.0,
      "text": "like mourning."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 159880.0,
      "end_time": 161736.0,
      "text": "Sound like one morning I could wake up"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 161760.0,
      "end_time": 164816.0,
      "text": "and see my son as a repeat of last week&#39;s story."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 164840.0,
      "end_time": 166736.0,
      "text": "Sound like I could wake up and realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 166760.0,
      "end_time": 169256.0,
      "text": "the death of my daughter wouldn&#39;t even be newsworthy."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 169280.0,
      "end_time": 172496.0,
      "text": "So you can&#39;t tell me that Sandra Bland is the only Black woman"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 172520.0,
      "end_time": 175960.0,
      "text": "whose violence deserves more than our silence."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 175120.0,
      "end_time": 177736.0,
      "text": "What about our other dark-skinned daughters in distress"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 177760.0,
      "end_time": 179536.0,
      "text": "whose deaths we have yet to remember?"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 179560.0,
      "end_time": 180776.0,
      "text": "What about our children"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 180800.0,
      "end_time": 183776.0,
      "text": "whose lives don&#39;t fit neatly between the lives of your genders?"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 183800.0,
      "end_time": 185936.0,
      "text": "See, apparently, nothing is a great protector"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 185960.0,
      "end_time": 188240.0,
      "text": "if you come out of a body that looks like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 188720.0,
      "end_time": 192616.0,
      "text": "See, there is something about being Black in America"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 192640.0,
      "end_time": 194576.0,
      "text": "that has made motherhood sound"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 194600.0,
      "end_time": 196760.0,
      "text": "like something I&#39;m not sure I look forward to."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 197920.0,
      "end_time": 203536.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve written too many poems about dead Black children to be naïve"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 203560.0,
      "end_time": 207920.0,
      "text": "about the fact that there could one day be a poem written about my kids."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 208600.0,
      "end_time": 211720.0,
      "text": "But I do not want to be a mother who gave birth to poems."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 212480.0,
      "end_time": 215550.0,
      "text": "I do not want a stanza for a son"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 215800.0,
      "end_time": 217256.0,
      "text": "nor a line for a little girl"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 217280.0,
      "end_time": 220280.0,
      "text": "nor a footnote for a child who doesn&#39;t fit into this world."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 220960.0,
      "end_time": 222176.0,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 222200.0,
      "end_time": 224416.0,
      "text": "I do not want children who will live forever"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 224440.0,
      "end_time": 226176.0,
      "text": "in the pages of poetry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 226200.0,
      "end_time": 228335.0,
      "text": "yet can&#39;t seem to outlive"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 228360.0,
      "end_time": 229576.0,
      "text": "me."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 229600.0,
      "end_time": 236120.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 238720.0,
      "end_time": 240976.0,
      "text": "I was invited to the TEDWomen conference"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 241000.0,
      "end_time": 242200.0,
      "text": "to perform a poem."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 243240.0,
      "end_time": 246760.0,
      "text": "But for me, poetry is not about art and performance."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 247440.0,
      "end_time": 249560.0,
      "text": "It is a form of protest."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 250640.0,
      "end_time": 251896.0,
      "text": "Yesterday,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 251920.0,
      "end_time": 253576.0,
      "text": "during rehearsal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 253600.0,
      "end_time": 255656.0,
      "text": "I was told that there had been"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 255680.0,
      "end_time": 258920.0,
      "text": "two to three recent TED Talks about Black Lives Matter."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 259959.0,
      "end_time": 263455.0,
      "text": "That maybe I should cut down my TED Talk"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 263480.0,
      "end_time": 266800.0,
      "text": "so it could \"just\" be about Reproductive Justice."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 267280.0,
      "end_time": 269655.0,
      "text": "But that poem and this talk"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 269680.0,
      "end_time": 272760.0,
      "text": "is fundamentally about my inability to separate the two."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 273920.0,
      "end_time": 275136.0,
      "text": "I was 21 years old --"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 275160.0,
      "end_time": 282160.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 283360.0,
      "end_time": 286280.0,
      "text": "I was 21 years old when Trayvon Martin was murdered."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 287360.0,
      "end_time": 291560.0,
      "text": "Trayvon Martin, a 17-year-old Black boy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 291800.0,
      "end_time": 292616.0,
      "text": "a Black child,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 292640.0,
      "end_time": 294176.0,
      "text": "reminded me"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 294200.0,
      "end_time": 295736.0,
      "text": "reminded us"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 295760.0,
      "end_time": 298640.0,
      "text": "how little this nation actually values Black life."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 299760.0,
      "end_time": 301976.0,
      "text": "The hashtag #BlackLivesMatter"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 302000.0,
      "end_time": 304456.0,
      "text": "became the most recognized call"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 304480.0,
      "end_time": 306976.0,
      "text": "for Black people and our children"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 307000.0,
      "end_time": 309856.0,
      "text": "to live in safe environments and healthy communities"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 309880.0,
      "end_time": 311216.0,
      "text": "without fear"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 311240.0,
      "end_time": 314600.0,
      "text": "from violence from individuals or the state or government."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 315960.0,
      "end_time": 317455.0,
      "text": "Months later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 317480.0,
      "end_time": 319656.0,
      "text": "when George Zimmerman was not held responsible"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 319680.0,
      "end_time": 321736.0,
      "text": "for murdering Trayvon Martin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 321760.0,
      "end_time": 323296.0,
      "text": "I heard Sybrina Fulton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 323320.0,
      "end_time": 324880.0,
      "text": "Trayvon Martin&#39;s mother, speak."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 326160.0,
      "end_time": 329216.0,
      "text": "Her testimony so deeply impacted me"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 329240.0,
      "end_time": 331240.0,
      "text": "that I found myself constantly asking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 332280.0,
      "end_time": 335950.0,
      "text": "what would it mean to mother in the United Stated of America"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 335120.0,
      "end_time": 336320.0,
      "text": "in this skin?"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 337400.0,
      "end_time": 338856.0,
      "text": "What does motherhood really mean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 338880.0,
      "end_time": 341160.0,
      "text": "when for so many who look like me"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 341400.0,
      "end_time": 343400.0,
      "text": "it is synonymous with mourning?"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 345400.0,
      "end_time": 346695.0,
      "text": "Without realizing it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 346720.0,
      "end_time": 349856.0,
      "text": "I had begun to link the Reproductive Justice framework"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 349880.0,
      "end_time": 351719.0,
      "text": "and the Movement for Black Lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 352800.0,
      "end_time": 354896.0,
      "text": "As I learned more about Reproductive Justice"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 354920.0,
      "end_time": 356296.0,
      "text": "at Women With A Vision,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 356320.0,
      "end_time": 360560.0,
      "text": "and as I continued to be active in the Movement for Black Lives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 360800.0,
      "end_time": 363880.0,
      "text": "I found myself wanting others to see and feel these similarities."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 364760.0,
      "end_time": 366776.0,
      "text": "I found myself asking:"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 366800.0,
      "end_time": 369576.0,
      "text": "Whose job is it in times like this"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 369600.0,
      "end_time": 372760.0,
      "text": "to connect ideas realities and people?"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 374280.0,
      "end_time": 376856.0,
      "text": "I want to dedicate this talk and that poem"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 376880.0,
      "end_time": 378320.0,
      "text": "to Constance Malcolm."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 379800.0,
      "end_time": 381695.0,
      "text": "She is the mother of Ramarley Graham"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 381720.0,
      "end_time": 383296.0,
      "text": "who was another Black child"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 383320.0,
      "end_time": 385000.0,
      "text": "who was murdered before their time."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 386320.0,
      "end_time": 388160.0,
      "text": "She reminded me once over dinner,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 388400.0,
      "end_time": 390296.0,
      "text": "as I was struggling to write that poem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 390320.0,
      "end_time": 392216.0,
      "text": "that it is the artist&#39;s job"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 392240.0,
      "end_time": 394936.0,
      "text": "to unearth stories that people try to bury"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 394960.0,
      "end_time": 397440.0,
      "text": "with shovels of complacency and time."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 398840.0,
      "end_time": 400135.0,
      "text": "Recently,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 400160.0,
      "end_time": 401400.0,
      "text": "Toni Morrison wrote,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 402360.0,
      "end_time": 404136.0,
      "text": "\"In times of dread,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 404160.0,
      "end_time": 406560.0,
      "text": "artists must never choose to remain silent."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 407400.0,
      "end_time": 409536.0,
      "text": "There is no time for self-pity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 409560.0,
      "end_time": 410920.0,
      "text": "no room for fear.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 412200.0,
      "end_time": 414135.0,
      "text": "Yesterday, during rehearsal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 414160.0,
      "end_time": 415576.0,
      "text": "when I was told that I should"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 415600.0,
      "end_time": 418976.0,
      "text": "\"maybe cut the Black Lives Matter portion from my talk,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 419000.0,
      "end_time": 420880.0,
      "text": "I found myself fearful for a moment."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 421800.0,
      "end_time": 424336.0,
      "text": "Fearful that again our stories were being denied"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 424360.0,
      "end_time": 426480.0,
      "text": "the very stages they deserve to be told on."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 427600.0,
      "end_time": 430280.0,
      "text": "And then I remembered the words I had just spoken."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 431320.0,
      "end_time": 433176.0,
      "text": "\"In times of dread,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 433200.0,
      "end_time": 436120.0,
      "text": "artists must never choose to remain silent."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 437120.0,
      "end_time": 439336.0,
      "text": "There is no time for self-pity."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 439360.0,
      "end_time": 446120.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 447600.0,
      "end_time": 450216.0,
      "text": "There is no time for self-pity."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 450240.0,
      "end_time": 451840.0,
      "text": "And no room for fear.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 452560.0,
      "end_time": 454656.0,
      "text": "And I have made my choice."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 454680.0,
      "end_time": 456580.0,
      "text": "And I am always choosing."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 457120.0,
      "end_time": 458576.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 458600.0,
      "end_time": 465800.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}